author: wtopstaff
title: Matt Kuchar 2nd after 1st round of Fiji International
text:
By The Associated Press October 15, 2015 4:20 am 
SUVA, Fiji (AP) — American Matt Kuchar shot a two-over 74 in blustery conditions Thursday to hold joint second-place after the first round of the Fiji International. 
The leaderboard at the jointly-sanctioned PGA Tour of Australasia and the OneAsia Tour event was dominated by Australian players. 
Josh Geary led after shooting an even-par 72, two strokes ahead of compatriots Daniel Nisbet, Nick Cullen, Alistair Presnall and R.J. Caracella, plus Kuchar, who had three birdies against five bogeys. 
Kuchar, who arrived from South Korea where he had played in the winning United States team at the Presidents Cup, said the gusty conditions at the Natadola Bay resort meant “it was purely about survival out there.” 
Fijian-born Vijay Singh was in a tie for 33rd at six over. Topics:
